## 🧠 Code Explained — How It Actually Works

---

### 📦 Libraries Used

```cpp
#include <SoftwareSerial.h>   // Bluetooth communication on pins 2,3
#include <Servo.h>            // Controls servo motor on pin 10
```

🔵 **SoftwareSerial** — Arduino Uno has only one hardware serial port
(used by USB). SoftwareSerial creates a second serial port on any
digital pins. Here we use D2 (RX) and D3 (TX) for Bluetooth.

🔵 **Servo** — Controls the SG90 servo that rotates the ultrasonic
sensor left and right for scanning.

---

### 📍 Pin Setup

```cpp
#define IN1 4  #define IN2 5   // Left motors
#define IN3 6  #define IN4 7   // Right motors
#define BUZZER 8               // Active buzzer
#define LED    9               // Headlight LED
#define SERVO_PIN 10           // Servo signal wire
#define TRIG   11              // Ultrasonic trigger
#define ECHO   12              // Ultrasonic echo
```

🗺️ Think of this as the map. Every component has its own
dedicated Arduino pin. Changing a wire? Just change the
number here — no need to hunt through the whole code.

