### 📡 How Distance Is Measured

```cpp
long getDistance() {
  digitalWrite(TRIG, LOW);
  delayMicroseconds(4);
  digitalWrite(TRIG, HIGH);   // Send ultrasonic pulse
  delayMicroseconds(10);
  digitalWrite(TRIG, LOW);
  long dur = pulseIn(ECHO, HIGH, 30000);  // Wait for echo
  total += (dur == 0) ? 300 : dur * 0.034 / 2;
}
```

📡 **How ultrasonic sensing works:**

Power ON
↓
Servo sweeps: CENTER → LEFT → RIGHT → CENTER
(alignment confirmation)
↓
Send 'V' from Bluetooth app
↓
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│  AUTO_FORWARD                   │
│  Motors running forward         │
│  Ultrasonic checks distance     │
│  every loop iteration           │
└────────────┬────────────────────┘
│ Object detected < 35cm
↓
Motors STOP
Buzzer BEEPS 400ms
↓
Servo → LEFT (160°)
Wait 500ms
Read distance → store as distLeft
↓
Servo → RIGHT (20°)
Wait 500ms
Read distance → store as distRight
↓
Servo → CENTER (90°)
Wait 350ms
↓
🧠 DECIDE:
┌────────────────────────────────┐
│ distLeft > distRight?          │
│   → Turn LEFT                 │
│ distRight > distLeft?          │
│   → Turn RIGHT                │
│ Both < 25cm (both blocked)?    │
│   → REVERSE 600ms             │
│   → Scan LEFT + RIGHT again   │
│   → Pick whichever is larger  │
│   → Turn that way             │
└────────────────────────────────┘
↓
Turn for 800ms
↓
Forward for 800ms (clear obstacle)
↓
Servo → CENTER
↓
Back to AUTO_FORWARD ↺



