### 📱 Bluetooth Mode Switching

```cpp
case 'V':
  autonomousMode = true;    // 🤖 Robot takes over
  forward();
  break;

case 'v':
  autonomousMode = false;   // 👨 You take over
  stopMotors();
  break;
```

🔄 **Two modes, one robot:**
- **Manual BT Mode** — You drive. Robot just listens to commands.
  No sensors, no servo, no auto anything.
- **Autonomous Mode** — Robot drives itself. Bluetooth only
  listens for `V`/`v`/`M` to switch modes. All other commands
  ignored while autonomous.

