### ⚠️ Why Servo Detach Matters

```cpp
// Entering autonomous — attach servo
scanner.attach(SERVO_PIN);

// Exiting autonomous — detach servo
scanner.write(SERVO_CENTER);
delay(400);
scanner.detach();   // ← THIS IS CRITICAL
```

⚡ **The conflict:**
Arduino Uno has limited hardware timers. Both the Servo
library and SoftwareSerial (Bluetooth) share **Timer1**.
When servo stays attached permanently, it disrupts the
timer and Bluetooth commands randomly stop working.

✅ **The fix:** Attach servo ONLY during autonomous mode.
Detach when returning to manual mode. This frees Timer1
completely for Bluetooth — same as if servo never existed.
